50|$|Kahn's work {{focuses on}} the social imaginary. Like many {{constitutional}} theorists, Kahn is interested in what makes law legitimate. Unlike most constitutional theorists, <b>his</b> <b>answer</b> <b>is</b> phenomenological: legitimacy {{is something that we}} experience, not something that can be guaranteed by theoretical accounts of law.|$|R
