2500|$|Porsche, Penske, and Donohue quickly {{started the}} {{development}} of the 917-30, complete with a reworked aerodynamic [...] "Paris" [...] body and a 5.4-liter turbocharged flat-12 engine whose output could be adjusted between approximately 1,100 and 1,500 bhp by turning a boost knob located in the cockpit. During {{the development of}} this motor, the German Porsche engineers often asked Donohue if the motor finally had enough power. <b>His</b> <b>answer</b> <b>was</b> [...] "it will never have enough power until I can spin the wheels {{at the end of the}} straightaway in high gear." ...|$|E
